    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-08T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-08T11:00:00-05:00" n="100"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d100">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Pacific War/748: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gade</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-08T10:00:00-06:00"
                            >December 8, 1941—10 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 2:03 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>105. Department’s circular telegram of December 7, 10 p.m. In reply to the oral
                    communication, the Foreign Minister handed me a copy of a telegram which is
                    being sent by President Martinez to President Roosevelt and which in translation
                    reads as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“I consider that the Japanese attack on Hawaii and Manila is absolutely
                            unjustified and contrary to the principle of law and treatment due a
                            country with which she was at peace. National Assembly is meeting today
                            to study the unusual case and to declare war on aggressor nation.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>A similar message is being forwarded from the Foreign Minister to the Secretary
                    of State.<note n="54" xml:id="d100fn1">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <p>The National Assembly is expected to convene at noon today.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gade</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
